# VIM

## Vim motions

### Horizontal

h - left
l - right

w, W - jump to beginning of a word/WORD
b, B - jump to back to the begining of the word/WORD
e, E - jump to end of a word/WORD
ge, gE - jump back to the end of the previous word/WORD

f{character} - jump to first instance of a {character} in that line
F{character} - jump back to first instance of a {character} in that line
t{character} - jump just before to first instance of a {character} in that line
T{character} - jump just before back to first instance of a {character} in that line

f{character}; - go to next instance of that character
f{character}, - go to previous instance of that character

0 - first character in a line
^ - first non blank cahracter of a line
$ - end of a line
g_ - first non blank character at the end of a line

### Vertical

j - up
k - down

} - jump paragraph down
{ - jump paragraph up
CTRL-D - move and scroll half the page down
CTRL-U - move and scroll half the page up

/{pattern} - search for a pattern forward
?{pattern} - search for a pattern backward
n - move to next pattern
N - move to previous pattern

### File movements

gd - go to deffinition
gf - go to a file in an import

gg - top of the file
{line}gg - specific line
G - enf of a file

ctrl-{ - collapse code block
ctrl-} - expand code block

### Scrolling

zt - current line to top of screen
zz - current line to center of screen
zb - current line to bottom of the screen

## Vim Operations

{operator}{count}{motion}

d - delete
dG - delete all lines after cursor
dd - delete entire line
D - delete in line from the cursor
d{motion} - deletes based on motion, for example `d2w` deletes 2 words or `dt;` deletes everything up to ;

u - undo
ctrl-r - redo

f- find
c - change
t - until


